data.Name: SoMo
data.Bio: Joseph Somers-Morales (born September 11, 1987), known by his stage name SoMo, is an American R&B and pop singer-songwriter. Born in Austin TX, USA he began his professional music career in 2011, gaining notoriety on YouTube by releasing original music and cover songs from popular recording artists such as Chris Brown, The Weeknd, and Drake. In 2013, he signed a recording contract with Republic Records, and released remastered versions of his 2012 mixtape My Life and debut single "Ride". His self-titled debut album SoMo was released in 2014. Read more on Last.fm
